%e A007673 A pair of coin vectors gives a solution if every nonempty subset sum has a different ratio. (1,2,1,0) and (4,0,1,1) is a solution for 4 mints using 4+2+1+1=8 coins because 1:4, 2:0, 1:1, 0:1, (1+2):(4+0)=3:4, (1+1):(4+1)=2:5, (1+0):(4+1)=1:5, (2+1):(0+1)=3:1, (2+0):(0+1)=2:1, (1+0):(1+1)=1:2, (1+2+1):(4+0+1)=4:5, (1+1+0):(4+1+1)=2:6, (2+1+0):(0+1+1)=3:2, (1+2+0):(4+0+1)=3:5, (1+2+1+0):(4+0+1+1)=4:6 are all distinct ratios.
